      },
      "date": "2013-08-30 03:21:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nBig problem with this patch is it really leaks lock structures as every subsequent io request is not able to match previous, e.g.:\ndd if=/dev/zero of=/mnt/lustre/file bs=4096 count=10000\n\nresults in:\nccc_lock_kmem      10000  10030     64   59    1 : tunables   32   16    8 : slabdata    170    170      0 : globalstat   10616  10026   170    0 \t\t   0    0    0    0    0 : cpustat   9263    737      0      0\nlov_lock_link_kmem  10000  10050     56   67    1 : tunables   32   16    8 : slabdata    150    150      0 : globalstat   10501  10021   150    0 \t\t   0    0    0    0    0 : cpustat   9228    772      0      0\nlov_lock_kmem      10000  10020    128   30    1 : tunables   32   16    8 : slabdata    334    334      0 : globalstat   10607  10020   334    0 \t\t   0    0    0    0    0 : cpustat   9241    759      0      0\ncl_lock_kmem       10001  10001   4096    1    1 : tunables   24   12    8 : slabdata  10001  10001      0 : globalstat   10001  10001 10001    0 \t\t   0    0    0    0    0 : cpustat      0  10001      0      0\n\n\nwhich is a disaster",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
